AngloGold Ashanti, Gold Fields Fall as Precious Metal Declines From Record

-- B y   S t e p h e n   G u n n i o n
-- 
2011-07-19T16:35:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-19/anglogold-ashanti-hits-10-week-high-amid-gold-s-rally-beating-gold-fields.html
AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (ANG) , Africa’s
largest gold producer, and  Gold Fields Ltd. (GFI)  slid after the
precious metal retreated from a record.  AngloGold declined 0.4 percent to 312.76 rand at the 5 p.m.
close of trading in Johannesburg. Gold Fields, Africa’s second-
largest producer, dropped 0.7 percent to 108.30 rand.  Gold futures for August delivery fell $1.70 to $1,600.70 at
11:03 a.m. on the Comex in New York. The metal had gained in the
previous 10 sessions, the longest rally since January 1980.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Gunnion in Johannesburg at 
 sgunnion@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
